request.description:
Connect after creating a task to receive real-time step-by-step updates.

Auth: Add header  Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Keep-alive: send {"type": "ping"} → server replies {"type": "pong"}

── STANDARDISED EVENT ENVELOPE ──
Every event has this shape:
{
  "event":      "<event_name>",
  "task_id":    "<uuid>",
  "agent_name": "Email Agent",
  "step":       3,
  "title":      "Sending email",
  "detail":     "To harideepak@krypsos.tech",
  "data":       { ...raw details... }
}
status_changed events also include: "status": "completed|failed|waiting_approval"

── EVENT NAMES ──
  step_started    — LLM thinking OR tool about to run
  step_finished   — tool result received
  status_changed  — task status changed (approval_needed / completed / failed)
  step_output     — partial streaming output (reserved for future use)

── EXAMPLE EVENTS ──
step_started (thinking):
  { "event": "step_started", "title": "Thinking", "detail": "Planning next action (step 1)" }

step_started (tool call):
  { "event": "step_started", "title": "Sending email", "detail": "To harideepak@krypsos.tech" }

step_finished:
  { "event": "step_finished", "title": "Got result", "detail": "Sending email completed" }

status_changed (approval needed):
  { "event": "status_changed", "status": "waiting_approval", "title": "Waiting for approval", "detail": "Send Email requires your review" }

status_changed (completed):
  { "event": "status_changed", "status": "completed", "title": "Task complete", "detail": "<result preview>" }

Typical use: connect immediately after POST /tasks/create/, use title+detail to drive UI labels, use status_changed to update progress bar and status chip.

